    {
      "id": "bridge-rendering-smoke-guide",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Bridge Rendering Smoke Test",
      "position": { "x": -460, "y": -260 },
      "width": 1260,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Bridge Rendering Smoke Test\n\nThis graph exists to catch non-standard bridge rendering.\n\n## What Should Be True\n\n- Stored bridge nodes (`type: bridge`) and legacy bridge-mode ports (`type: port` + `data.mode: bridge`) render the *same* bridge chrome.\n- The left glyph is the referenced artifact's icon view (`node.web.icon` / `icon.web`) when available.\n- If no icon view is exposed, the bridge falls back to a small glyph based on `resourceKind`.\n\n## Checks\n\n1. Compare \"Stored Bridge\" cards vs \"Bridge-Mode Port\" cards: they should look the same.\n2. Confirm the icon slot is populated for node-classes that expose an icon view.\n3. Confirm endpoint-only legacy bridge still resolves and renders.\n4. Confirm graph-target bridges render with disabled create (until graph bridging is implemented).\n"
      }
    },
